21/05/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Four candidates are running for the top post in the main opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP), following an approval process Saturday (May 19th). According to an SDP statement, they are SDP deputy chairperson and acting leader Zeljka Antunovic, two senior officials Tonino Picula and Zoran Milanovic, and the head of the Zagreb branch, Milan Bandic. The party plans an extraordinary congress on June 2nd to elect a successor to Ivica Racan, who died of cancer in late April. (HRT, Index.hr - 19/05/07)
